subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.

Stethusa klimschi

differs from 

S. dichroa

in the following characters: the lack of subbasal impressions of the terminal antennal article; the apex of median lobe is narrower in ventral view (

Figs. 
48­49

; 
29­30
) and straight in lateral view (

Figs. 
50­51

; 
31­ 32
); the lack of the distal spines of the internal sac (

Figs. 
54

; 
38­39
); the shape of the spermatheca (

Figs. 
57

; 
41­42
); and the lack of a female accessory sclerite.

Stethusa klimschi

differs from 

S. spuriella

in having a larger body size; straight apex of the median lobe (in lateral view; 

Figs. 
50­51

; 
65­66
); and a longer spermatheca (

Figs. 
57

; 
70
).
